《'''難以置信'''》（{{lang-en|Hard to Believe}}）是一部2015年由[[美國|美國]][[公共電視網_(美國)|PBS公共電視台]]製作的[[紀錄片|紀錄片]]，透過{{who|多名專家}}調查，披露[[中國共產黨|中國共產黨]]執政當局被指控從被關押中的[[法輪功|法輪功]]學員身上[[器官移植|摘取]][[肝臟|肝臟]]、[[腎臟|腎臟]]、[[眼角膜|眼角膜]]、[[心臟|心臟]]等器官，當摘除器官時，這些人仍活著；並形成了一條完整的器官產業鏈，被害者還包括一些[[維族|維族]][[穆斯林|穆斯林]]、[[地下教會|地下教會]][[基督徒|基督徒]]。英國《[[每日郵報|每日郵報]]》指，本片是通過長期持久的調查剖析了「為什麼國際社會對於『當代最災難性的人權侵犯行為』選擇視而不見」的第一部電影。<ref name=DM1005>{{cite news|author1=Imogen Calderwood For Mailonline|title=Thousands of religious prisoners in China had their livers, kidneys and corneas ripped out while they were ALIVE to sell to 'transplant tourists', claims new film|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3257383/Thousands-religious-prisoners-China-livers-kidneys-corneas-ripped-ALIVE-sell-transplant-tourists-claims-new-film.html|agency=MailOnline英國每日郵報|date=2015-10-05|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20151004235300/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3257383/Thousands-religious-prisoners-China-livers-kidneys-corneas-ripped-ALIVE-sell-transplant-tourists-claims-new-film.html|archivedate=2015-10-04|language=en|quote=[http://www.epochtimes.com/b5/15/10/4/n4542652.htm 中文編譯報導]|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref name=Mirror>{{cite news|author1=John Shammas|title=Thousands of religious prisoners in China 'have organs ripped out while ALIVE to sell to transplant tourists'|url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/thousands-religious-prisoners-china-have-6567660|agency=英國《每日鏡報》Mirror|date=2015-10-03|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20151216144259/http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/thousands-religious-prisoners-china-have-6567660|archivedate=2015-12-16|deadurl=yes}}</ref>《生物倫理學探討期刊》稱「本片對於從事器官捐獻和移植、人權、醫療、倫理及法律業的人們至關重要；忽视弱势群体的需求会侵蚀人性和破坏公众的信任。」<ref name="JBI">{{cite journal|title=Hard to Believe-Produced by Ken Stone and Irene Silber, 2015, Swoop Films and Stone Soup Productions (New York, 56 minutes, unrated)|journal=生物倫理學探討期刊 (Journal of Bioethical Inquiry)|date=2016-06|issue=Volume 13, Issue 2|pages=pp 353–356|url=http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11673-016-9717-1||quote=This documentary is extremely important for those involved in organ donation and transplantation, human rights, healthcare, ethics, and the law. A failure to address the needs of vulnerable people erodes humanity and destroys public trust. |language=en}}</ref>曾獲選十大影响力科學家的美國生物倫理學者[[亚瑟·卡普兰|亚瑟·卡普兰]]稱「该片是对我們這个時代最嚴重的人權迫害之一的一个十分重要、及時、令人深感不安的讲述。」<ref>{{cite news|title=“Hard To Believe” But All Too Real: New Documentary Exposes Crime of Executing Political Prisoners for Organ Transplantation- New DVD Release Today|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/10/prweb12991261.htm|agency=PRWEB|quote=Leading U.S. ethicist and Founding Director of the Division of Medical Ethics at NYU, Arthur Caplan, PhD. says the film, Hard To Believe, is “an important, timely, and deeply disturbing account of one of the great human rights abuses of our time.”|date=2015-09-29}}</ref><ref name="BW">{{cite news|title=New Documentary HARD TO BELIEVE to Be Released Today on DVD|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/New-Documentary-HARD-TO-BELIEVE-to-Be-Released-Today-on-DVD-20150929|agency=Broadway World百老匯世界|date=2015-09-29|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105095028/http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/New-Documentary-HARD-TO-BELIEVE-to-Be-Released-Today-on-DVD-20150929|archivedate=2016年11月5日|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>此片說明了，在數量龐大的證據面前，國際社會為何未能採取行動。<ref name="TDB">{{cite news|author1=Nina Strochlic|title=Does China Harvest Organs From Living Prisoners?|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/09/29/does-china-harvest-organs-from-living-prisoners.html|agency=[[每日野獸|The Daily Beast]]|date=2015-09-30|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/articles/2015/09/29/does-china-harvest-organs-from-living-prisoners.html|archivedate=2016-07-05|quote=[http://www.watchinese.com/article/2015/20492 中文編譯報導]}}</ref><ref name="ABC">{{cite news|author1=Andrew West|title=Hard To Believe: forced organ harvesting in China and Australia's moral obligations(9分鐘廣播，專訪Dr. Katrina A. Bramstedt，澳洲邦德大學倫理學家 )|url=http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/religionandethicsreport/hard-to-believe-forced-organ-harvesting-in-china-falun-gong/6889082?|agency=ABC[[澳洲廣播公司|澳洲廣播公司]]|date=2015-10-28|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505093113/http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/religionandethicsreport/hard-to-believe-forced-organ-harvesting-in-china-falun-gong/6889082|archivedate=2016-05-05|language=en|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

==製作==
美國《圖書館視頻評論期刊》影評稱「強力推薦這一教育性人權紀錄片。」<ref name="Librarian">{{cite journal|author1=P. Morehart|title=Hard to Believe|journal=Video Librarian, The Video Review Magazine for Libraries,（圖書館視頻評論期刊）|date=2016-05-06|issue=31|quote=“Also including a study guide, this illuminating, often deeply unsettling PBS-aired documentary is highly recommended.”}}</ref>兩度[[艾美獎|艾美獎]]得主、導演肯•斯通（Ken Stone）表示：「我們所做的就是探索為甚麼這些報導和紀錄片得到的關注如此之少。許多人提供了如此強有力的證據，但是他們總是被人忽視。」<ref name=DM1005/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bernardo |first1=Mary Geanelli |title=“Hard to Believe” documentary aims to raise awareness of organ harvesting |url=https://wou.edu/westernhowl/hard-believe-documentary-aims-raise-awareness-organ-harvesting/ |accessdate=2021-10-22 |work=The Western Howl |date=2017-03-01}}</ref>

紀錄片討論了調查記者[[伊森·葛特曼|伊森·葛特曼]]和諾貝爾和平獎被提名人[[大衛·麥塔斯|大衛·麥塔斯]]律師和加拿大前國務秘書[[大衛·喬高|大衛·喬高]]進行的獨立調查。葛特曼向媒體表示「在面對暴行時，人們總習慣不去正視。只有當它已經過去了之後，人們才會承認一件殘暴的事情。從我們用了多長時間，才承認對猶太人大屠殺，你就會明白。這種事情發生了一次又一次。」<ref name=DM1005/>

本片在[[習近平|習近平]]赴紐約出席聯合國峰會期間，在美國PBS公共電視網播出、發行DVD。美國PBS播出此片逾40次。<ref>{{cite news|title=Docu film exposes alleged Chinese prisoners’ organs being harvested while still alive|url=http://kickerdaily.com/posts/2015/10/docu-film-chinese-prisoners-organs/|agency=Kicker Daily News|date=2015-10-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104225617/http://kickerdaily.com/posts/2015/10/docu-film-chinese-prisoners-organs/|archivedate=2016-11-04}}</ref>在2016年於香港召開世界器官移植大會前公映。<ref>{{cite news|title=New Documentary “Hard to Believe” Probes Transplant Crimes Before World Transplant Congress in HK|url=http://www.bioethics.com/archives/28516|agency=Bioethics.com轉載Digital Journal|date=2015-07-22|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017143502/http://www.bioethics.com/archives/28516|archivedate=2015-10-17|language=en}}</ref>

